Uses of Package
edu.rit.crst

  • Packages that use edu.rit.crst 
    Package Description
    edu.rit.aes
    Package edu.rit.aes contains implementations of the AES family of block ciphers for testing by the CryptoStat library.
    edu.rit.crst
    Package edu.rit.crst contains the core CryptoStat classes and interfaces.
    edu.rit.sha1
    Package edu.rit.sha1 contains an implementation of the SHA-1 hash function for testing by the CryptoStat library.
    edu.rit.sha2
    Package edu.rit.sha2 contains an implementation of the SHA-2 family of hash functions for testing by the CryptoStat library.
    edu.rit.sha3
    Package edu.rit.sha3 contains an implementation of the SHA-3 family of hash functions and the SHAKE family of extensible output hash functions for testing by the CryptoStat library.
  • Classes in edu.rit.crst used by edu.rit.aes 
    Class and Description
    Computation
    Class Computation is the abstract base class for an object that performs a computation on the GPU.
    Function
    Class Function is the abstract base class for a cryptographic function.
  • Classes in edu.rit.crst used by edu.rit.crst 
    Class and Description
    BitGroup
    Class BitGroup is the abstract base class for an object that generates a series of output bit groups for a cryptographic Function.
    CombiningGenerator
    Class CombiningGenerator is an abstract base class for an object that generates input values for a cryptographic Function.
    Computation
    Class Computation is the abstract base class for an object that performs a computation on the GPU.
    Function
    Class Function is the abstract base class for a cryptographic function.
    FunctionKernel
    Interface FunctionKernel specifies the interface for a GPU kernel function that evaluates a cryptographic Function on a series of inputs.
    Generator
    Class Generator is the abstract base class for an object that generates input values for a cryptographic Function.
    Test
    Class Test is the abstract base class for an object that performs odds ratio tests for a cryptographic Function.
    TestKernel
    Interface TestKernel specifies the interface for a GPU kernel function that computes the logarithms of the Bayes factors for all rounds and bit groups for a Test object.
    TestResult
    Class TestResult provides the Java equivalent of the CUDA testResult_t structure.
    TransformGenerator
    Class TransformGenerator is the abstract base class for an object that generates input values for a cryptographic Function.
